{"word":"G5495 - χείρ - cheír - khire - Hand","slug":"G5495","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">χείρ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>cheír"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>khire"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Hand"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C7;&#x03B5;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C1; - cheir</b> - <i>khire</i><p/>Perhaps from the base of <a href=\"#/G5494\">G5494</a> in the sense of its congener the base of <a href=\"#/G5490\">G5490</a> (through the idea of <i>hollowness</i> for grasping); the <i>hand</i> (literally or figuratively [<i>power</i>]; especially [by Hebraism] a <i>means</i> or <i>instrument</i>): - hand."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G5496\">G5496</a>, <a href=\"#/G5497\">G5497</a>, <a href=\"#/G5498\">G5498</a>, <a href=\"#/G5499\">G5499</a>, <a href=\"#/G5500\">G5500</a>, <a href=\"#/G886\">G886</a>"}]}